            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> roasted</strong> <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, half the<strong> flaked almonds</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> romesco sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: You'll serve this at room temperature so set this aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
